.ol-tag-consult p{color:rgba(255,255,255,.82);font-size:14px;line-height:1.58;margin:0 0 18px}
.ol-tag-consult .ol-tag-btn{width:max-content}
@media(max-width:899px){.ol-tag-hero{min-height:380px;background-position:center}.ol-tag-trust,.ol-tag-grid,.ol-tag-checks{grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr}.ol-tag-checks{align-items:start}.ol-tag-consult{grid-column:1/-1}.ol-tag-section__head{display:block}.ol-tag-section__head p{margin-top:8px}}
@media(max-width:599px){.ol-tag-hero{min-height:0;background:linear-gradient(180deg,rgba(13,28,20,.86),rgba(13,28,20,.58)),url({{ 'onelife-product-page-lifestyle-strip.jpg' | asset_url }}) center/cover no-repeat}.ol-tag-hero__inner{padding:30px 16px 34px;max-width:100%}.ol-tag-kicker{font-size:10.5px;margin-bottom:14px}.ol-tag-hero h1,.ol-tag-hero .ol-tag-hero__inner h1{font-size:clamp(31px,8.8vw,38px);line-height:1.05}.ol-tag-hero__lead{font-size:15.2px;line-height:1.45;max-width:100%}.ol-tag-hero__actions{display:grid;margin-top:20px}.ol-tag-btn{width:100%}.ol-tag-shell{padding:24px 16px 42px}.ol-tag-trust{grid-template-columns:1fr;margin-top:16px}.ol-tag-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr}.ol-tag-card{min-height:0}.ol-tag-checks{grid-template-columns:1fr}.ol-tag-panel,.ol-tag-consult{padding:18px}.ol-tag-consult .ol-tag-btn{width:100%}}
</style>

<main class="ol-tag-guide">
  <section class="ol-tag-hero">
    <div class="ol-tag-hero__inner">
      <p class="ol-tag-kicker">Product Tags</p>
      <h1>Shop tags help you shortlist faster.</h1>
      <p class="ol-tag-hero__lead">
        Use tags to shortlist faster.<br>
        Check the product label before purchase.
      </p>
      <div class="ol-tag-hero__actions">
        <a class="ol-tag-btn ol-tag-btn--light" href="/pages/shop">Shop Products</a>
        <a class="ol-tag-btn ol-tag-btn--ghost" href="https://wa.me/27713744910?text=Hi%2C%20I%20need%20help%20checking%20a%20product%20tag%20or%20ingredient" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Ask a Consultant</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="ol-tag-shell">
    <div class="ol-tag-trust" aria-label="How product tags should be used">
      <div class="ol-tag-trust__item">
        <strong>Supplier-based guidance</strong>
        <span>Tags are based on supplier, manufacturer and product information available to One Life Health.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="ol-tag-trust__item">
        <strong>Label first</strong>
        <span>Ingredients, allergen warnings and directions on the product pack remain the final reference.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="ol-tag-trust__item">
        <strong>Expert help available</strong>
        <span>Our consultants can help you check a product if you are unsure about suitability.</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ol-tag-note">
      <strong>Important:</strong> product tags are a shopping guide only. Always check the product label, ingredients list and allergen information before purchase or use. If you have allergies, are pregnant or breastfeeding, take medication, have a medical condition, or are unsure whether a product is suitable, ask a One Life Health consultant or a qualified healthcare professional first.
    </div>

    <section class="ol-tag-section">
      <div class="ol-tag-section__head">
        <h2>What each tag means</h2>
        <p>These definitions explain how to read the tags on One Life product cards. They are not medical, allergen or formulation guarantees.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ol-tag-grid" aria-label="Product tag meanings">
        <article class="ol-tag-card">
          <span class="ol-tag-chip">Dietary</span>
          <h3>Gluten Free</h3>
          <p>Used where supplier or product information indicates a gluten-free claim or no gluten-containing ingredients. Always check the allergen statement.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="ol-tag-card">
          <span class="ol-tag-chip">Dietary</span>
          <h3>Sugar Free</h3>
          <p>Used where supplier or product information indicates no added sugar or a sugar-free claim. Check the nutrition panel for sweeteners and total carbohydrates.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="ol-tag-card">
          <span class="ol-tag-chip">Allergen</span>
          <h3>Dairy Free</h3>
          <p>Used where product information indicates no dairy ingredients. If you have a dairy allergy, check the label for allergen and cross-contact warnings.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="ol-tag-card">
          <span class="ol-tag-chip">Lifestyle</span>
          <h3>Vegan</h3>
          <p>Used where supplier or product information indicates a vegan formulation. Check capsules, flavourings and additives if strict vegan suitability matters.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="ol-tag-card">
          <span class="ol-tag-chip">Lifestyle</span>
          <h3>Vegetarian</h3>
          <p>Used where supplier or product information indicates vegetarian suitability. Check capsule type and any animal-derived ingredients on the label.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="ol-tag-card">
          <span class="ol-tag-chip">Origin</span>
          <h3>SA Made</h3>
          <p>Used where product or supplier information indicates South African manufacturing, production or packing. It does not automatically mean every ingredient is locally sourced.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="ol-tag-card">
          <span class="ol-tag-chip">Ingredient claim</span>
          <h3>Organic</h3>
          <p>Used where product information includes an organic claim. Check the product label for the exact organic certification or ingredient-level claim.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="ol-tag-card">
          <span class="ol-tag-chip">Ingredient claim</span>
          <h3>Non-GMO</h3>
          <p>Used where supplier or product information indicates a non-GMO claim. Check the packaging for the exact scope of the claim.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="ol-tag-card">
          <span class="ol-tag-chip">Dietary</span>
          <h3>Keto</h3>
          <p>Used as a low-carb shopping aid where available product information supports keto-friendly use. Check macros and serving size against your own plan.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="ol-tag-section ol-tag-checks">
      <div class="ol-tag-panel">
        <h2>How to use tags safely</h2>
        <ul class="ol-tag-list">
          <li>Use tags to narrow your search, not as the only basis for purchase.</li>
          <li>Read the actual product label and ingredients before checkout and before use.</li>
          <li>Check allergen warnings, cross-contact warnings and serving directions.</li>
          <li>Confirm suitability with a consultant or healthcare professional if you are unsure.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="ol-tag-consult">
        <div>
          <h2>Need help checking a product?</h2>
          <p>Send us the product name or a label photo and we will help you confirm the ingredient and tag details before you buy.</p>
        </div>
        <a class="ol-tag-btn ol-tag-btn--light" href="https://wa.me/27713744910?text=Hi%2C%20I%20need%20help%20checking%20a%20product%20tag%20or%20ingredient" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Chat on WhatsApp</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</main>
